The Regional Centre on Small
Arms in the Great Lakes Region held a handover dinner at Double Tree by Hilton, Ngong Road. Outgoing executive secretary Theoneste Mutsindashyaka handed over to Elamin Elgadir. United Religions Initiative awarded the organisation the
prestigious 2018 Africa Peace Award in recognition of its
contribution to peace and development in Africa through interventions to
control proliferation of illicit small arms and light weapons. Present were Ambassador Mussie Hailu, Desiree Bakosa and Interpol URI Africa regional director Mussie Hailu and regional bureau head Gideon Kimilu.